    • Method Detail

      • syllabify

        public String syllabify(String phoneString)
        Deprecated. 
        Syllabify a phonetic string, marking syllable boundaries with dash characters in the output. If the input marks stressed vowels with a suffix "1", these marks are removed, and single quotes (') are inserted at the beginning of the corresponding syllable.
        Parameters:
        phoneString - the phone string to syllabify.
        Returns:
        a syllabified phone string, with space characters inserted between individual phone symbols

      • syllabify

        public LinkedList<String> syllabify(LinkedList<String> phoneList)
        Deprecated. 
        Syllabify a LinkedList of phones. This is an implementation of the syllabification rules by Jürgen Trouvain.
        Parameters:
        phoneList - phoneList
        Returns:
        a LinkedList of phone strings with inserted "-" strings at syllable boundaries.

      • correctStressSymbol

        protected void correctStressSymbol(LinkedList<String> phoneList)
        Deprecated. 
        For those syllables containing a "1" character, remove that "1" character and add a stress marker ' at the beginning of the syllable.
        Parameters:
        phoneList - phoneList

      • splitIntoAllophones

        @Deprecated
protected LinkedList<String> splitIntoAllophones(String phoneString)
        Deprecated. This duplicates (badly) AllophoneSet.splitAllophoneString(String); use that method instead.
        Convert a phone string into a list of string representations of individual phones. The input can use the suffix "1" to indicate stressed vowels.
        Parameters:
        phoneString - the phone string to split
        Returns:
        a linked list of strings, each string representing an individual phone

      • getAllophone

        @Deprecated
protected Allophone getAllophone(String phone)
        Deprecated. Use AllophoneSet.getAllophone(String) instead
        Get the Allophone object named phone; if phone ends with "1", discard the "1" and use the rest of the string as the phone symbol.
        Parameters:
        phone - phone
        Returns:
        allophoneset.getAllophone(phonesubstring(0, phone.length() - 1)) if this.removeTrailingOneFromPhones and phone.endsWith("1"), allophoneset.getAllophone(phonesubstring(phone) otherwise
